.TH "register_chrdev_region" 9 "register_chrdev_region" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
register_chrdev_region \- register a range of device numbers
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" register_chrdev_region
.BI "(dev_t from "  ","
.BI "unsigned count "  ","
.BI "const char *name "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "from" 12
the first in the desired range of device numbers; must include
the major number.
.IP "count" 12
the number of consecutive device numbers required
.IP "name" 12
the name of the device or driver.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Return value is zero on success, a negative error code on failure.
